questions.question: When writing a 1:M relationship class, there is no intermediate table to keep track of these relationships.
Which of the following is not a prerequisite for writing to M:N relationship classes in a file geodatabase using FME?
options: Your geodatabase already has the relationship class.
The relationship is M:N or an attributed relationship.
You have the license for an Esri ArcGIS product that allows you to write to file geodatabases.
Your workspace has a MNRelationshipCreator transformer.
